x4freetext: Cylindrical samples of natural isotopic abundance,
2.5 cm in diameter by 5.2 cm high
The detectors were used NE213 liquid
scintillators in bubble free thin aluminum
containers 5 cm in diameter by 15 cm high.
Deuteron-deuterium reaction with partially
polarized 2.9 MeV neutrons at an angle of 49 deg.
Polarization was estimated to be -0.15 +/- 0.01
Proton recoil spectra were recorded for each detector
Corrections were introduced for flux attenuation and
multiple scattering in the finite scatterer-detector
geometry using Monte-Carlo program due to B.Holmqvist,
B.Gustavsson,T.Wielding,Ark.Phys.34,481(1967).
For contribution from inelastic scattering due
to the finite energy resolution.
